{
  "text": "To be clear, we are computing power for a fixed value of the effect size, either \u2426 i or \u2426 . Several others [CITATION_1] have suggested computing power across a distribution of effect sizes because of uncertainty in the estimate of the effect sizes (usually sampling error).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "19888956"
